An Upper Area Court sitting in Kasuwan Nama, Jos, on Tuesday, sentenced a 40-year-old dry cleaner, Joseph John, to 15 years in prison for defiling an eight-year-old girl. The Judge,  Mr Lawal Suleiman, sentenced John after he pleaded guilty to a charge of defilement. Suleiman held that the convict should serve out his term without an option of fine. ALSO READ: Insecurity came in because we forgot our heritage —Olaniyan Court remands two men for allegedly kidnapping a housewife Applicant in court for attempting to steal car Court sentences mechanic to 10 months in prison for stealing… Five out of 10 kidnapped victims regain freedom in Osun He said that he hoped it would serve as a deterrent to those who would want to indulge in such an act. Earlier, the Prosecutor,  Mr Monday Dabit told the court that the case was reported on August 8, by one of Fumilayo Adeboyi of Gondola Jos, the girl‘s mother and the complainant. Dabit said the defendant, who resides at Nassarawa Gwong area of Jos, was caught touching the girl on her private parts. According to the prosecutor, the offence contravened the provision of Section 208 of the Penal Code of Northern Nigeria. The defendant had begged the court for mercy, saying it was the devil that pushed him into the act. Here is how i overcome QUICK RELEASE and make it BIGGER, STRONGER And LONGER with this NAFDAC APPROVED NATURAL REMEDY. Click now!!